In a message dated 12/22/02 10:52:14 PM Central Standard Time, 
wingedwarrior41@... writes:


&gt; Belthassan: Melchana, sitrep?
&gt; 
&gt; Melchana answered in nothing more than a whisper and in very short
&gt; sentences so as not to be discovered.
&gt; 
&gt; Melchana: Made noise. Trying diplomacy.
&gt; 
&gt; Gesper: Are you nuts?!? Since when have you been a diplomat?!?!
&gt; 
&gt; Had he been there, she would have knocked him unconscious. He was
&gt; lucky this time.


Maxima&#39;s eyes glanced aabout furiously. She was right, .. she did hear 
something for sure. She stopped in her tracks & crouched down, hiding in the 
shadows. Trying one of Ravage&#39;s old tricks. 

&gt; 
&gt; Belthassan: All right, but keep it very, very soft.
&gt; 
&gt; Melchana: Roger. Kick monkey for me.

Still & silent, she watched & waited.

&gt; 
&gt; She jumped down to the metallic floor and landed with a little noise.

Her optics glanced over to see a figure appear from a nook. 

&gt; 
&gt; Melchana: Hey, you can show up. I know you&#39;re there. I&#39;m not here to
&gt; hurt you unless you ask for it.
&gt; 
&gt; There was a reason Gesper and Belthassan had been reluctant to let her
&gt; play the diplomat. She was a hunter before anything and she knew it.
&gt; She was better with her claws than with her tongue.
&gt; 

Staying in the shadows. She watched this new creature. By the looks of it, 
they were similar to her, a mix of organic & cybernetic. 

&#39;Trans-organics!&#39; she thought. Was this a horrible experiment by the Quints? 
They attempted this long ago.  

&quot;You were very poor in stealth.&quot; She called out in a feline femme voice, with 
a slight deep sophistication to it. &quot;Are you Autobot or Decepticon? Or are 
you a pathetic Transorganic experiment created by the Quints?&quot; 

She stayed in the shadows, out of sight... for now. Waiting to see who this 
newcomer was & what they were. Her questions were mounting. 



